---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Interactive" description="Live mathematical visualizations powered by Pretext">
  <h1>Interactive Mathematics</h1>
  <p class="page-intro">
    Live visualizations of our computational results. Text layout powered by
    <a href="https://github.com/chenglou/pretext">Pretext</a> —
    measuring and flowing text without DOM reflows.
  </p>

  <section class="manifesto" id="manifesto-section">
    <div class="manifesto-text">
      <h2 class="m-reveal">How This Site Was Built</h2>

      <p class="m-reveal">A human picked the problems. An AI wrote the CUDA kernels. The human decided which results mattered. The AI managed the data pipeline. Neither could have done this alone.</p>

      <p class="m-reveal">That's not a grand statement about the future of mathematics — it's just what happened here. One person with a GPU cluster and an AI assistant produced computational results across a dozen open problems in number theory and combinatorics. Some of those computations would have taken months of manual coding. With AI collaboration, they took hours.</p>

      <div class="m-stats m-reveal">
        <div class="m-stat"><span class="m-num" data-value="27">0</span><small>Zaremba exceptions<br/>with A=&#123;1,2,3&#125;</small></div>
        <div class="m-stat"><span class="m-num" data-value="26400000000" data-display="26.4B">0</span><small>Kronecker coefficients<br/>for S₃₀</small></div>
        <div class="m-stat"><span class="m-num" data-value="30000000000" data-display="30B">0</span><small>class numbers<br/>computed</small></div>
        <div class="m-stat"><span class="m-num" data-value="1048575">0</span><small>Hausdorff dimensions<br/>all subsets of &#123;1,...,20&#125;</small></div>
      </div>

      <p class="m-reveal">These are computational results, not proofs. None of this work has been peer-reviewed. The code is open, the data is open, and the reproduction commands are on every page — so anyone can check our work. That's the point. We're not claiming authority. We're publishing the computations and inviting scrutiny.</p>

      <p class="m-reveal">The AI didn't have mathematical insight. It had speed. It could write a CUDA kernel in minutes, debug it against test cases, optimize memory access patterns, and manage uploads to Hugging Face — all tasks that are tedious for a human but trivial for an AI. The human decided <em>what</em> to compute and <em>why</em> it mattered. The AI decided <em>how</em> to compute it efficiently.</p>

      <div class="m-pullquote m-reveal"><span>The bottleneck in computational mathematics has always been engineering, not ideas.</span></div>

      <p class="m-reveal">There are thousands of open conjectures where the next step is "compute this for larger values and see what happens." Most of those computations never get done because writing the GPU kernel, setting up the data pipeline, and publishing the results is more work than most researchers want to do for a speculative computation. AI collaboration removes that friction. The ideas were always there. Now they can be tested.</p>

      <p class="m-reveal">This site is an experiment in that process. Some of the results will turn out to be interesting. Some won't survive peer review. All of the data is here for you to use.</p>

      <p class="manifesto-cite m-reveal">— Cahlen Humphreys, 2026. Built with Claude.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
  // Scroll-triggered reveals + number counter animation
  (function() {
    var reveals = document.querySelectorAll('.m-reveal');
    var nums = document.querySelectorAll('.m-num[data-value]');
    var counted = new Set();

    function onScroll() {
      var vh = window.innerHeight;
      for (var i = 0; i < reveals.length; i++) {
        var el = reveals[i];
        var top = el.getBoundingClientRect().top;
        if (top < vh * 0.85) el.classList.add('visible');
      }
      // Animate numbers when visible
      for (var j = 0; j < nums.length; j++) {
        var n = nums[j];
        if (counted.has(n)) continue;
        if (n.getBoundingClientRect().top < vh * 0.85) {
          counted.add(n);
          animateNum(n);
        }
      }
    }

    function animateNum(el) {
      var target = parseInt(el.getAttribute('data-value'));
      var display = el.getAttribute('data-display');
      var duration = 1200;
      var start = performance.now();
      function step(now) {
        var t = Math.min((now - start) / duration, 1);
        t = 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3); // ease out cubic
        var current = Math.round(target * t);
        if (display) {
          // Format as "26.4B" style
          var ratio = t;
          el.textContent = display.replace(/[\d.]+/, function(m) {
            return (parseFloat(m) * ratio).toFixed(m.includes('.') ? 1 : 0);
          });
        } else {
          el.textContent = current.toLocaleString();
        }
        if (t < 1) requestAnimationFrame(step);
      }
      requestAnimationFrame(step);
    }

    window.addEventListener('scroll', onScroll, { passive: true });
    onScroll(); // initial check
  })();
  </script>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Zaremba Witness Distribution</h2>
    <p>
      Drag the slider to explore how the witness ratio α(d)/d concentrates
      around 0.171 as d grows. Each bubble is a value of d, sized by its
      CF length, colored by max partial quotient.
      <a href="/findings/zaremba-witness-golden-ratio/">Finding →</a>
      <a href="/experiments/zaremba-conjecture-verification/">Experiment →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="witness-viz">
      <canvas id="witness-canvas"></canvas>
      <div class="viz-controls">
        <label>
          <span>Max d:</span>
          <input type="range" id="witness-max-d" min="100" max="10000" value="1000" step="100">
          <span id="witness-d-label" class="mono">1000</span>
        </label>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Spectral Gap Landscape</h2>
    <p>
      The congruence spectral gaps σ<sub>m</sub> for all 1,214 square-free moduli
      up to m=1999. Hover over any point to see the modulus, factorization,
      and gap value. The red dashed line marks the Bourgain-Kontorovich threshold.
      <a href="/findings/zaremba-spectral-gaps-uniform/">Finding →</a>
      <a href="/experiments/zaremba-transfer-operator/">Experiment →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="spectral-viz">
      <canvas id="spectral-canvas"></canvas>
      <div id="spectral-tooltip" class="tooltip"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>CF Tree Explorer</h2>
    <p>
      The continued fraction tree with partial quotients in &#123;1, &hellip;, 5&#125;.
      Each path from root to leaf gives a Zaremba denominator. Watch the
      tree grow and see how quickly it covers the integers.
      <a href="/findings/zaremba-conjecture-proved/">Finding →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="tree-viz">
      <canvas id="tree-canvas"></canvas>
      <div class="viz-controls">
        <label>
          <span>Depth:</span>
          <input type="range" id="tree-depth" min="1" max="9" value="5">
          <span id="tree-depth-label" class="mono">6</span>
        </label>
        <button id="tree-animate" class="viz-btn">Animate Growth</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Zaremba Density Phase Transition</h2>
    <p>
      For digit set A, the Zaremba density measures what fraction of integers d have a
      coprime a/d with all CF partial quotients in A. A sharp phase transition occurs
      between A=&#123;1,2&#125; (58%) and A=&#123;1,2,3&#125; (99.997%). The transition is controlled
      by the Hausdorff dimension crossing 1/2.
      <a href="/findings/zaremba-density-phase-transition/">Finding →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="density-viz">
      <canvas id="density-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Class Number Distribution</h2>
    <p>
      Distribution of class numbers h(d) for 2.74 billion real quadratic fields
      Q(√d) with d&nbsp;∈&nbsp;[10<sup>9</sup>,&nbsp;10<sup>10</sup>). Dominated by powers of 2
      (genus theory). The Cohen-Lenstra prediction of 75% with h=1 is far from realized
      at this scale — convergence is non-monotone.
      <a href="/findings/class-number-convergence/">Finding →</a>
      <a href="/experiments/class-numbers-real-quadratic/">Experiment →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="classnum-viz">
      <canvas id="classnum-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="interactive-section">
    <h2>Hausdorff Dimension Spectrum</h2>
    <p>
      Hausdorff dimension dim<sub>H</sub>(E<sub>A</sub>) for every subset
      A&nbsp;⊆&nbsp;&#123;1,…,10&#125;, grouped by cardinality |A|. Each dot is one of
      the 1,023 nonempty subsets. Adding digit 1 has the largest effect on
      dimension — 5 digits including 1 beat 9 digits without it.
      <a href="/findings/hausdorff-digit-one-dominance/">Finding →</a>
      <a href="/experiments/hausdorff-dimension-spectrum/">Experiment →</a>
    </p>
    <div class="viz-container" id="hausdorff-viz">
      <canvas id="hausdorff-canvas"></canvas>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .page-intro {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-style: italic;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    .page-intro a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--accent); }

    .manifesto {
      margin-bottom: 4rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 6px;
      background: var(--surface);
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .manifesto-text {
      padding: 3rem 3.5rem;
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .manifesto h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      color: var(--ink);
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .manifesto p {
      color: var(--ink-secondary);
      margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
    }
    .manifesto strong {
      color: #e8c47a;
    }
    .manifesto-cite {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      text-align: center;
    }

    /* Scroll reveal */
    .m-reveal {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(20px);
      transition: opacity 0.7s ease, transform 0.7s ease;
    }
    .m-reveal.visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }

    /* Stagger children */
    .m-reveal:nth-child(2) { transition-delay: 0.05s; }
    .m-reveal:nth-child(3) { transition-delay: 0.1s; }
    .m-reveal:nth-child(4) { transition-delay: 0.15s; }

    /* Pull quotes */
    .m-pullquote {
      margin: 2.5rem 0;
      padding: 0;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .m-pullquote span {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: #e8c47a;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      position: relative;
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.5rem 0;
    }
    .m-pullquote span::before,
    .m-pullquote span::after {
      content: '';
      display: block;
      width: 40px;
      height: 1px;
      background: rgba(232,196,122,0.3);
      margin: 0.8rem auto;
    }

    /* Glowing highlight */
    .m-glow {
      color: #e8c47a;
      text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(232,196,122,0.15);
    }

    /* Stats counter row */
    .m-stats {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
      gap: 1.2rem;
      margin: 2.5rem 0;
      padding: 1.5rem 0;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(232,196,122,0.1);
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(232,196,122,0.1);
    }
    .m-stat {
      text-align: center;
    }
    .m-stat .m-num {
      display: block;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      color: #e8c47a;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }
    .m-stat small {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.4;
      display: block;
    }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .manifesto-text { padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
      .m-stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
      .m-pullquote span { font-size: 1.1rem; }
    }

    .interactive-section {
      margin-bottom: 4rem;
    }
    .interactive-section h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    .interactive-section p {
      color: var(--ink-secondary);
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .viz-container {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      position: relative;
    }

    canvas {
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
      display: block;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .viz-controls {
      margin-top: 1rem;
      display: flex;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      align-items: center;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .viz-controls label {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.6rem;
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .viz-controls input[type="range"] {
      width: 200px;
      accent-color: var(--accent);
    }

    .mono { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent); font-size: 0.82rem; }

    .viz-btn {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      background: transparent;
      color: var(--accent);
      border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 30%, transparent);
      padding: 0.35rem 0.8rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 160ms ease;
    }
    .viz-btn:hover { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 8%, transparent); }

    .tooltip {
      display: none;
      position: absolute;
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--rule);
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--ink);
      pointer-events: none;
      z-index: 10;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
  </style>

  <div id="load-interactive"></div>
</Base>
